  "title": "Plunder on Kohlma",
  "summary": "Drawn by rumors of outlaw treasure, four parties converge on the ravaged Bando Gora moon of Kohlma: the lone scavenger Sekes, the CSA VicePrex Morrison Van Sen with his science team, a cigarra-smoking Umbaran woman, and the stealthy Scaven. As they pick their way across the temple ruins, the moon's deathstick-mutated natives swarm them, forcing running gun battles in which Sekes blasts and grenades his way forward and Van Sen calls an orbital strike that vaporizes the doomed Umbaran and her tormentors. Sekes loots the ancient vault only to find drug-cult junk and mummified bounties, dismissing it as overrated, while Scaven ignores the treasure entirely and pries up a Germanium plaque whose forgotten script matches the writing from his own cryotube. With the temple burning and the hunger-mob massing at every exit, each survivor scrambles to escape the collapsing ruin.",
